-Mv2DeprecationDisabledDialogBrowserTest.InvokeUi
-Mv2DeprecationKeepDialogBrowserTest.InvokeUi

# This test fails because of the following CHECK in identity_test_utils.cc:
# !primary_account_info.IsEmpty()
-ManagedUserNoticeUIDialogPixelTest.InvokeUi_default/*
-ManagedUserNoticeUIWindowPixelTest.InvokeUi_default/*

# These tests fail because in identity_test_utils.cc waiting for
# identity_manager->AreRefreshTokensLoaded() times out.
-AvatarToolbarButtonPromoBrowserTest.*
-AvatarToolbarButtonPromoClickBrowserTest.*
-AvatarToolbarButtonSignedOutPromoBrowserTest.SignedOutPromoTriggeredOnStartupAfterDelayExpired 

# These tests fail because kPrerender2 feature is disabled.
-MediaEngagementPreThirdPartyCookieDeprecationBrowserTest.Ignored

# These tests fail because the primary account consent level is null instead of
# signin::ConsentLevel::kSignin
-All/AvatarToolbarButtonEnterpriseBadgingWithSyncPromoParamsBrowserTest.*

# This test fails because we override RegionalCapabilitiesServiceClientLinux::
# FetchCountryId to get locale from device instead of the variations service.
-RegionalCapabilitiesServiceFactoryBrowserTestForVariationsCountry.GetCountryId/FR

# This test fails because we disable PermissionElement origin trial.
-All/PermissionElementOriginTrialBrowserTest.WithOriginTrialToken/BaseEnabled_BlinkDisabled

# These tests fail because Brave enables screen farbling
# (kBraveBlockScreenFingerprinting) by default on desktop, which modifies
# screen dimension values returned to web content.
-HeadlessModeProtocolBrowserTest_OzoneScreenSizeOverride.OzoneScreenSizeOverride
-MultiscreenWindowManagementPermissionContextTest.IsExtendedCrossOriginAllow
-MultiscreenWindowManagementPermissionContextTest.IsExtendedCrossOriginDeny
-MultiscreenWindowManagementPermissionContextTest.IsExtendedSameOriginAllow
-WindowManagementTest.OnCurrentScreenChangeEvent
-WindowManagementTest.OnScreensChangeEvent
-WindowManagementTest.ScreenDetailedOnChange
-WindowManagementTest.ScreenDetailedOnHdrHeadroomChange

# Chromium test: intermittent RunLoop timeout in DevTools paused debugger focus
# mechanism. The test relies on an async chain (DebuggerPaused event → SourcesPanel
# module loading → bringToFront IPC) that sometimes doesn't complete before the
# test timeout. Already disabled upstream on Windows ASAN (crbug.com/337141755).
# 0.2% upstream flake rate over 30 days per LUCI Analysis. No Brave-specific code
# affects this path.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/53358
-DevToolsProcessPerSiteTest.PausedDebuggerFocus

# Chromium test: Blink's IdlenessDetector requires 500ms of renderer thread quiet
# time to fire NetworkBecameIdle. Brave's cosmetic filters inject MutationObserver
# and setInterval(500ms) polling on all pages, generating continuous renderer tasks
# that prevent the quiet window from completing. 1.1% upstream flake rate over 30
# days per LUCI Analysis.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/54021
-PageStabilityMetricsMinWaitTest.NetworkAndMainThreadIdleDelayed
# Same root cause as above: Brave's cosmetic filters prevent the IdlenessDetector's
# 500ms quiet window from completing, causing the 4s page stability timeout to fire
# before NetworkBecameIdle. 1% upstream flake rate over 30 days per LUCI Analysis.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/54205
-PageStabilityMetricsTest.NetworkAndMainThreadIdle

# These tests fail on Linux because kPromptForDownload defaults to true,
# triggering the GTK file chooser dialog which causes g_malloc leaks
# detected by LSan on ASAN builds and timeouts.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/52572
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/52649
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/52569
-All/PDFPluginDisabledTest.DirectNavigationToPDF/*
-ChromeMojoProxyResolverFactoryBrowserTest.*
-PluginResponseInterceptorURLLoaderThrottleBrowserTest.DownloadPdf

# These fail because OsIntegrationTestOverride::GetShortcutPath and
# OsIntegrationTestOverride::IsRunOnOsLoginEnabled on Linux hard-codes "chrome-"
# into the shortcut name but our shortcut starts with "brave-".
-ShortcutSubManagerBrowserTest.CleanUpEphemeralProfileDeletesShortcuts

# Chromium test: fixture sets kGlicActorPageStabilityTimeout to 30s but doesn't
# set kActorObservationDelayTimeout (defaults to 10s). On slow CI, the 10s
# overall timeout fires while still in kWaitForPageStability, causing the state
# to skip kWaitForLoadCompletion and jump directly to kDone. 0.5% upstream flake
# rate over 30 days per LUCI Analysis. No Brave chromium_src overrides affect
# the ObservationDelayController code path.
# https://github.com/brave/brave-browser/issues/54159
-ObservationDelayControllerTest.UsePageStabilityForSameDocumentNavigation

